          "message": "The guard `if (manager && currentRendererId === rendererId)` throws an error only when the same renderer ID re-enables, but the comment says 'A different renderer type... is trying to enable JS root components.' This is contradictory: the condition checks for equal rendererId, not different. If a different renderer type (different rendererId) calls enableJSRootComponents, the condition is false, so no error is thrown and the manager is silently overwritten. This could lead to a scenario where two different renderer types both claim to manage dynamic root components, violating the stated unsupported multi-host assumption.",
